===========================================================================
$NetBSD$

    To use punjab, several items must be set in rc.conf.

    The available variables are:
	punjab_jid	[Jabber ID of the service, default "punjab"]
	punjab_secret	[shared secret with the S2S]
	punjab_rhost	[ost of the Jabber service router, default "localhost"]
	punjab_rport	[port of the Jabber service router, default 5347]

    punjab_secret and punjab_ips variables are required.

    ex:
	punjab_jid=bosh.jabber.example.org
	punjab_secret=JabberSecret
	punjab_rhost=jabber.example.org
	punjab_rport=5347

===========================================================================
